patthana23.1:0.2_0: (These should be expanded as in the previous discourse.)
patthana23.1:1.1_0: Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!
patthana23.1:13.1_0: There is no such thing as pleasant, painful feeling to arise.
patthana23.1:13.1_1: There is no such thing as pleasant feeling ...
patthana23.1:14.1_0: Nor do they arise because of the unskillful feelings.
patthana23.1:14.1_1: No matter what is unskillful, painful, and neutral feelings arise.
patthana23.1:15.1_0: There is no answer to a principle of pain, pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by skillful.
patthana23.1:16.1_0: No matter what is unskillful, nor is a principle.
patthana23.1:17.1_0: No matter what is unskillful, nor are they different things.
patthana23.1:18.1_0: There is no such thing as pleasant feeling and unskillful, and not with suffering.
patthana23.1:2.1_1: No to cause a condition for pleasant feeling ...
patthana23.1:3.1_1: Not committed to the joy of pleasant feeling ...
patthana23.1:6.1_0: Not committed to the practice of pleasant feeling ...
patthana23.1:7.1_0: No to be skilled in pleasant feeling ...
